      "side": 1,
      "message": "I had a discussion with bsalomon@ on a previous CL where he advocated for `static constexpr`s even inside function definitions. PTAL http://review.skia.org/303657 at the discussion on #509.\n\nPersonally I would agree with your description above and would lean towards not having the `static` if we didn\u0027t have an existing codebase style to maintain. I don\u0027t think there\u0027s a particularly strong rationale for it (which is probably why my phrasing here doesn\u0027t really sell it) besides consistency with existing code/\"when in Rome\". I think one thing that caused me to soften my position was looking at godbolt; the `static` actually seems to generate equally-tight or tighter code, so at least it\u0027s doing no harm. https://godbolt.org/z/18KPGE for an example where the static actually helps.\n\nI could just remove the sentence about `static` entirely if we don\u0027t want to take a position at all here.",
